</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Aggression_Management_Best_Practices_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1707493578" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Aggression_Management_Best_Practices_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1707493578 1536w" width="1751" height="1167" alt="Aggression Management Best Practices - Dr Richard Dune -.png__PID:53e74f51-9c55-4d91-ac5c-ccdc9a79683a" title="Aggression Management Best Practices - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-149_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-150_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Satura_ via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-152_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Violence and aggression in health and social care settings can manifest in various forms, from verbal abuse to physical attacks, significantly impacting the mental and physical health of healthcare workers.<br><br>The NHS Staff Survey (2022) highlighted that 14.7% of staff experienced physical violence from patients or the public in the past year, a figure that rises alarmingly in sectors like ambulance services (45.8%).
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-154_">What is violence and aggression?
</h3><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-156_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Violence and aggression encompass a broad spectrum of behaviours. The Health and Safety Executive (HSE) defines work-related violence as "any incident in which a person is abused, threatened, or assaulted in circumstances relating to their work."
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-158_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-159_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-160_">Legislative framework and best practices
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safety_Protocols_for_Health_Professionals_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1707493749" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Safety_Protocols_for_Health_Professionals_-_Dr_Richard_Dune.png?v=1707493749 1536w" width="1748" height="1041" alt="Safety Protocols for Health Professionals - Dr Richard Dune -.png__PID:72433d00-edaf-4e73-b497-f21fd5916237" title="Safety Protocols for Health Professionals - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-162_"/><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-163_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by fauziEv8 via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-165_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Below are some of the key legislative, regulatory and best practice recommendations for health and social care providers concerning managing workplace aggression and violence:
</p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-167_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-168_"><b>Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974</b> - This act requires employers to ensure the health, safety, and welfare of their employees, including protective measures against violence and aggression.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-170_"><b>Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999</b> - Mandates risk assessments for violence and the implementation of measures to mitigate identified risks.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-172_"><b>Care Quality Commission (CQC) Guidelines</b> -  Emphasise the necessity for health and social care providers to have systems in place to manage patient behaviour that challenges, ensuring safety and quality of care.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-174_"><b>NICE Guidelines (NG10)</b> - Offer comprehensive recommendations on short-term management of violence and aggression, focusing on de-escalation techniques and minimising the use of restraint.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-176_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-177_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-178_">Violence and aggression - Tackling the issue head-on
