</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-188_"><b>Training and support</b> - Equipping staff with the skills to de-escalate potentially violent situations through communication, understanding, and empathy is fundamental. Ongoing support, including post-incident counselling, ensures the resilience of healthcare workers.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-190_"><b>Collaborative approach</b> - Engaging with law enforcement, mental health professionals, and community services can provide a holistic strategy to address the root causes of aggression.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-192_"><b>Reporting and learning</b> - Encouraging a culture of reporting incidents without fear of blame is essential for learning and improving safety protocols.
